  <ability>
    <abilitytitle>Alchemy</abilitytitle>
    <abilityid>lore.alchemy</abilityid>
    <abilityclass>Non-Combat</abilityclass>
    <abilitydescription>
      <p>
	Alchemy is concerned with the creation of chemical substances,
	the creation of cures for various diseases, the creation of solvents (acids),
	liquid fire, dies, gunpowder, etc.
      </p>
	
      <p>
	Two, as yet, unattained goals of alchemy are the transmutation of lead into gold,
	and the creation of an elixir of immortality.  
      </p>
    </abilitydescription>
    
    <abilitylevels>
      <abilitylevel>
        <levelnumber>1</levelnumber>
        <defaultlore>7</defaultlore>
        <defaultmartial>0</defaultmartial>
        <defaultgeneral>7</defaultgeneral>
        <prereqabilitylevel>lore.maths_1</prereqabilitylevel>
        <successes>3</successes>
        <attempts>3</attempts>
        <check>Std 2d8 vs default 10</check>	
	<leveldescription>
	  <p>
	    The character can check to Manufacture explosives,
	    acids, dyes, gunpowder etc.  Can identify many chemical substances.
	  </p>
	</leveldescription>
      </abilitylevel>

      <abilitylevel>
        <levelnumber>2</levelnumber>
        <defaultlore>7</defaultlore>
        <defaultmartial>0</defaultmartial>
        <defaultgeneral>7</defaultgeneral>
        <successes>3</successes>
        <attempts>3</attempts>
        <check>Std 2d8 vs default 8</check>		
	<leveldescription>
	  <p>
	    The character call themselves an Apothecary, and can prepare poisons
	    and medicines for certain diseases in addition to the abilities from first level.
	  </p>
	</leveldescription>
      </abilitylevel>

    </abilitylevels>
  </ability>



  <ability>
    <abilitytitle>Law (Society)</abilitytitle>
    <abilityid>lore.law</abilityid>
    <abilityclass>Non-Combat</abilityclass>
    <abilitydescription>
      <p>
	An understanding of the law grants the character insight into the way society
	works.  The practice of law invariably leads to the heart of industry and
	the seats of power.  Characters may be able to discern the motive behind
	political machinations and they may be able to cite a legal precedent in
	order to compell or cease certain courses of events in a civilized society.	
      </p>

      <p>
	Law is the study of the laws of a particular society.  The study of the
	laws of one society is not necessarilly applicable to another.  When choosing
	the law ability the player must specify which legal system they are studying.
      </p>	
    </abilitydescription>
    <abilitylevels>

      <abilitylevel>
        <levelnumber>1</levelnumber>
        <defaultlore>7</defaultlore>
        <defaultmartial>0</defaultmartial>
        <defaultgeneral>7</defaultgeneral>
        <successes>2</successes>
        <attempts>1</attempts>
        <check>Std 2d8 vs default 12</check>		
	<leveldescription>
	  <p>
	    Good, but not professional, understanding of the law of some land.  Usually,
	    the characters homeland.  Some understanding of the laws in surrounding regions.
	  </p>
	</leveldescription>
      </abilitylevel>


      <abilitylevel>
        <levelnumber>2</levelnumber>
        <defaultlore>7</defaultlore>
        <defaultmartial>0</defaultmartial>
        <defaultgeneral>7</defaultgeneral>
        <successes>2</successes>
        <attempts>1</attempts>
        <check>Std 2d8 vs default 10</check>		
	<leveldescription>
	  <p>
	    Professional level understanding and possibly experience with the law in a region.
	  </p>
	</leveldescription>
      </abilitylevel>
    </abilitylevels>
  </ability>




